Vice President Biden hosted a lunch meeting with leaders and officials from 11 nations to discuss nuclear security and proliferation issues. The purpose was to address the global risks of nuclear terrorism and ensure the security of nuclear materials. The participants emphasized the relationship between nuclear security and the development of nuclear energy. The Vice President stated that peaceful nuclear uses can thrive in a world where nuclear risks are reduced and non-proliferation rules are respected. He also mentioned that the United States is ready to assist any state in good standing with its non-proliferation obligations that is interested in pursuing nuclear energy.